      <h1 align="center">Graduate Seminars</h1>
      <h2 align="center">Screen Media Research </h2>
      <p>DR L DOVEY and PROF W D TROTTER, Screen Media Research Seminar (1S, 2 hours, odd weeks) Tu. 5, <em>Centre for Research in the Arts, Social Sciences, and Humanities, 17 Mill Lane </em></p>
      <p> The purpose of these seminars is to encourage as broad a debate as possible about &lsquo;screen media&rsquo; (primarily film and tv) and the cultures in which they are embedded. The programme will combine papers given by distinguished visiting speakers with &lsquo;reading group&rsquo; sessions whose purpose is to develop a common language for the discussion of screen media and cultures. </p>
      <p> <strong>1 May </strong> John Akomfrah, one of the founders of the Black Audio Film Collective in Britain, will discuss his career as a film-maker. The talk will be illustrated with clips from his films
      <p>Chair: Dr Lindiwe Dovey
      <p>&nbsp; </p>
